HEADWORD: Malva sylvestris
<hw>Malva sylvestris</hw><pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
species name of the tall mallow, an erect or decumbent Old World
perennial with axillary clusters of rosy-purple flowers; introduced into
the U. S.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tall mallow, high mallow, cheese,
cheeseflower.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malvaviscus</ent>⟦br⟧
